{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1679597533,"nonce":"REW6qRdwsRwy+6vg6hW+RNN2jKs=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5ho62P","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5205","origin":"github"},"title":"Roary: adjust the command line to prevent intermediate file deletion?","message":"tool_id: toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repos/iuc/roary/roary/3.13.0+galaxy2\n\nHow the problem presents:\nTool can fail when many inputs are given -- or not fail and just produce emtpy outputs, in particular the core alignment.\n\nPossible solution (guess!):\nAdd in `-z` to the command string?\nhttps://github.com/sanger-pathogens/Roary/issues/519\n\nAlternative solutions might include:\nHave the tool just warn about GFFs left out of the final result, instead of failing?\nOutput a better log? When the tool produces empty outputs users are confused about why, and if not \"red\" failure no bug report options, so may be a more common issue than we know about.\n\nReferences:\n* Several user issues at the developer's repo. https://github.com/sanger-pathogens/Roary/issues. Search with \"proteome\" or \"core alignment\".\n* Questions at the Ghelp forum, example: https://help.galaxyproject.org/t/roary-troubleshooting-version-3-13-0-galaxy2-or-later/. More found by searching with keyword \"roary\" -- some were about the prior file naming issue but even once adjusted (by user or via the updated wrapper) -- the mystery about why empty results remains. \n* Older tracking ticket: https://github.com/galaxyproject/usegalaxy-playbook/issues/293#issuecomment-1255461595","files":null}]}